Include mobile workers

Enable Contact Centre staff to easily access integrated, organisation-wide information and route requests to appropriate departments whether working remotely or onsite, from a laptop or a mobile device (whether service requests are made online, by phone or in person).
Connected citizens

Empower citizens with mobile apps that facilitate direct access to service systems and teams, in reporting local incidents and community effecting scenarios.   Provide precise, engaging and relevant feedback, encouraging citizens to further utilise apps, directly resulting in faster issue resolution that improves the community as a whole.
Increase service quality

Earlier and more detailed awareness of tasks created directly by citizens means more immediate resolution.  Task instruction and completion is undertaken by field workers without the need to return to the office, allowing ‘feet on the street’ resources to have greater capacity to improve the quality and availability of the services they provide.
